# summary of phd thesis in holy quran and its sciences. title of the
~~thesis: interpretation (tafsear) of abe-eshak el-shatebi of holy quarn
~~(collection and study) prepared by: mohamed ben abd-allah ben salah al-
~~dala this thesis was defended in wednesday (8-2-1427 h) in el-emam
~~mohamed ben saudi university, faculty of religious studies, rayed. the
~~candidate was awarded phd with the first grade of honor. abstract of the
~~thesis: 1 ... in this thesis, the candidate collects the abe-eshak el-
~~shatebi interpretation (tafsear) of the holy quarn from selected number
~~of published books like, mowafakat and etesam, elmakased elshafia and
~~fatawa el-shatebi. 2 the abe-eshak el-shatebi interpretation reaches
~~about 239 positions in the holy quarn, which talked about more than
~~three hundreds verses. in addition, the candidate discusses more than
~~300 problems discussed by abe-eshak el-shatebi. 3 the studies revealed
~~that the el-shatebi was highly interested in various interpretations oh
~~holy quarn specially the reasons behind each verses, as well as the
~~benefits underlying these verses. in addition, he was highly concerned
~~by establishing relationships between holy quarn verses and hadith. 4
~~... organization of the thesis the thesis includes the following points:
~~??research proposal ??introduction ??context of studies ??two sections
~~??conclusion ??appendices ----------------------------------------------
~~----------------------------------------------------------------------
~~??context of studies the interpretation characters in the era of abe-
~~eshak el-shatebi. first section: PageV01P0001
